This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society) because it focuses on a programming environment and online community for young people. It may also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it includes information on comments and communication within the community. Additionally, it could be categorized as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) because it involves analyzing social interactions within an online community. It may also fit into cs.SD (Software Engineering) because it includes information on the source code of the software used to operate the website. Finally, it could be categorized as cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) because it involves studying the interactions between young people and a programming environment.
